  "instructions": [
    "Combine pomegranate molasses, dried apricots, pistachios, caramel sauce, sour cherries, honey, water, rose water, ground cinnamon, and ground ginger in a large saucepan.",
    "Heat the mixture over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until the sugar has dissolved and the mixture is hot but not boiling.",
    "Add the chickpeas and cook for an additional 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a serving dish and drizzle with lemon juice and olive oil.",
    "Refrigerate for at least 2 hours to allow the flavors to meld together.",
    "Serve chilled, garnished with additional pistachios and rose petals if desired."
  ],
